Rules-Requires-Root: no
X-Build-Environment: This package is built in a container that provides
 libtriton-jit-dev (from the FlagOS apt repo) and a CUDA-aware PyTorch.
 The build is done once via scikit-build-core; the resulting wheel is
 split into the binary packages below.

# ---- Phase 1 binary package ----------------------------------------
# python3-flag-gems carries everything (Python + bundled liboperators.so)
# until the cmake-only split (Phase 2) lands.

Package: python3-flag-gems
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${python3:Depends},
         ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         python3-numpy,
         python3-yaml,
         python3-sqlalchemy,
         python3-packaging
# python3-torch is pulled in automatically via ${python3:Depends} from
# pyproject.toml, so it is intentionally omitted from Recommends to avoid
# a redundant (and conflicting) declaration.
Recommends: python3-flagtree-nvidia
Description: FlagGems GPU operator library (Python module)
 FlagGems is a GPU operator library written in Triton, providing a
 drop-in replacement for many torch.* operations with custom-tuned
 kernels.
 .
 This package contains the Python bindings, the Triton kernel sources,
 and (for Phase 1 of packaging) the bundled liboperators.so. A future
 release will split the C++ runtime into libflaggems and the headers
 into libflaggems-dev so that downstream C++ consumers can link
 against the operators library without installing the Python module.

# ---- Phase 2 binary packages (DECLARED, not yet built) -------------
# These stanzas ship the C++ side as standalone packages once the
# split lands. Until then, debian/rules does NOT produce them — the
# control file has the names reserved so future PRs are additive.
